# Neuro-Connector Bot — General Rules

## Stack
- Python 3.x, python-telegram-bot 20.7, PostgreSQL 15 + asyncpg, OpenRouter API
- aiohttp for web server (mini_app)
- Docker + Docker Compose for all environments

## Async / Await
- All I/O operations must be async (`async/await`)
- Use `async with` for context managers
- Wrap external calls in `try...except` with `logger.error()`
- Set timeouts on all external HTTP requests (30s default)

## Code Style (PEP 8)
- 4 spaces indentation, max 100 chars per line
- `snake_case` for functions/variables, `PascalCase` for classes
- Type hints on all function signatures:
  ```python
  async def save_user(self, telegram_id: int, first_name: str) -> None:
  ```

## Error Handling
- Always catch specific exceptions, never bare `except:`
- Log errors via `logger.error(f"Description: {e}")`
- NEVER expose internal errors to the client — return generic messages
- Set timeouts on external API requests (30s default)

## Security in Every Module
- All DB queries: parameterized only (`$1, $2`), NEVER f-strings with user input
- All public identifiers: UUID, never sequential IDs
- All user input: validate type, length, and format before processing
- All API responses: set proper `Content-Type`, never leak internal state

## OpenRouter API
- Endpoint: `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions`
- Always include `Authorization`, `Content-Type` headers
- Use `HTTP-Referer` and `X-Title` for tracking
- Audio transcription endpoint: `https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/audio/transcriptions`
- Limit prompt size to prevent abuse; truncate oversized inputs

## Logging
- Use Python `logging` module with named loggers per module
- Log levels: DEBUG for dev, INFO for production
- Include context in log messages (user_id, endpoint, action)
- NEVER log tokens, passwords, or personal data
